In Fig.1, it can be found that in patients with T1DM, exogenous insulin injection combined with oral glucocorticoids can effectively control glucose within a reasonable range, as compared with the strategy without glucocorticoids. Further, it can be found that the combined treatment strategy can avoid hypoglycemia. Fig.2 simulates the exogenous insulin injections in patients with T2DM combined with oral glucocorticoid hormone drugs treatment strategy. We can observe the effects of different initial value change. The relatively high glucose indicates low insulin and relatively low sugar patients are shown with high insulin. Such treatment strategy can achieve homeostasis which keeps the organism’s biological hormone in normal indicators. In Fig.3, we compared glucose concentrations in patients with T2DM treated by exogenous insulin alone and combination with glucocorticoids. Fig.4 and Fig.5 described a comparison of different insulin and glucocorticoid pulse volumes.Fig. 1
